events.description: The ruling Liberal Democratic Party secured a two-thirds supermajority in the lower house of the House of Representatives.
Japan's 10-year government bond yield rose 5 basis points to 2.27% following the election results.

facts.fact_text: Japan's 10-year government bond yield rose about 5 basis points to 2.27% on Monday.

evidences.evidence_text: Japan’s 10-year government bond yield rose about 5 basis points to 2.27% on Monday following the ruling Liberal Democratic Party’s historic victory.

facts.fact_text: The LDP coalition won 352 of the 465 seats in the House of Representatives.

evidences.evidence_text: Takaichi’s coalition won 352 of the 465 seats in the House of Representatives, according to public broadcaster NHK, with the LDP alone capturing 316 seats.

claims.claim_text: The election victory will likely weigh on the yen and Japanese government bonds.

evidences.evidence_text: This will likely to weigh on the yen and Japanese government bonds while potentially boosting equities.

claims.claim_text: The election outcome reinforced expectations for looser fiscal policy and potential tax cuts.

evidences.evidence_text: The outcome reinforced expectations for looser fiscal policy and potential tax cuts, developments that had unsettled Japanese financial markets in recent weeks

claims.claim_text: The supermajority gives Takaichi a mandate to pursue expansionary fiscal policies.

evidences.evidence_text: giving her a clear mandate to pursue expansionary fiscal policies.
